What is General Education?
1232: University of Paris, first Baccalaureate, all students study art, rhetoric, & logic
1877: Johns Hopkins, first major, all students study core courses before concentrating.
2021: The Great Plurality
Open Curriculum: no requirements for either core or majors, e.g., Brown
Great Books: no majors and only a core curriculum for all students, e.g. St. Johns College
Core Curriculum: traditional majors and the same core courses for all students, e.g., Columbia, Chicago
General Education: traditional majors and a common curriculum based on distribution requirements, e.g., NJCU
